comments: Towns (MIN) firms up on his right leg and marginal contact occurs as Reaves (LAL) moves over the pick.
Towns (MIN) momentarily brings his arm around Reaves' (LAL) left arm as Towns attempts to establish position away from the ball and the marginal contact dissolves shortly thereafter.
James (LAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Towns' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
James (LAL) takes less than 8 seconds to establish the ball in the frontcourt.
Schroder (LAL) firms up in Edwards' (MIN) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Hachimura (LAL) establishes himself in Conley's (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Towns (MIN) legally contests James' (LAL) perimeter jump shot attempt.

James' (LAL) shot attempt bounces off of the rim and makes contact with part of the basket that is behind the backboard. This part of the basket is considered out of bounds and possession is correctly awarded to Minnesota.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in Reaves's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Reaves (LAL) and Towns (MIN) engage away from the ball and marginal contact occurs as he slides his arm off of Towns.
Reaves (LAL) moves alongside Towns' (MIN) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the drive.
James (LAL) legally contests Conley's (MIN) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Anderson (MIN) places and promptly removes his hands from Schroder's (LAL) side as he sidesteps around Schroder during the rebounding opportunity. The contact on the play is marginal.
Davis (LAL) goes into the air in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Anderson (MIN).
James (LAL) and Conley (MIN) engage in the post and marginal contact occurs.
Towns (MIN) lowers his left arm down toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with James' (LAL) arm after the release of the pass.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Anderson (MIN) and Reaves (LAL) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Prince (MIN) briefly places and removes his hand from James' (LAL) right arm as he deflects the inbound pass. The contact on the play is marginal.
null
James (LAL) goes to the ground in pursuit of the loose ball and lower body contact occurs with Prince (MIN) that causes him to fall to the floor.
Davis (LAL) brings his arm forward and does not make contact with either Anderson (MIN) or the ball.
Anderson (MIN) loses control of his dribble and the ball bounces into the backcourt, where it is first touched by Anderson. Possession is properly awarded to Los Angeles.
Reaves (LAL) calls a timeout fewer than five seconds after receiving the ball from the official.
Russell (LAL) establishes himself in Edwards' (MIN) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Davis (LAL) and Anderson (MIN) engage as they move towards the basket and marginal contact occurs.
Towns (MIN) and James (LAL) come together during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Davis (LAL) closes out into Conley's (MIN) space and body contact occurs after the release that affects his follow-through.
Towns (MIN) firms up on his right leg and marginal contact occurs as Schroder (LAL) moves into the pick.
Hachimura (LAL) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Prince (MIN) steps into James' (LAL) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Towns (MIN) backs up as Davis (LAL) launches into the air to retrieve the pass and marginal contact occurs.
Towns (MIN) absorbs the marginal contact with Davis' (LAL) arm as he leans away from the offensive player during the layup attempt at the basket.

Davis (LAL) brings his arms up toward the basket during his shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Towns' (MIN) chin/head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in Reaves' (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Schroder (LAL) reaches in and makes hand on ball contact to dislodge the ball away from Edwards (MIN).
Schroder (LAL) deflects the ball and is the last player to touch it prior to going out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to MIN.
Schroder (LAL) and Towns (MIN) come together during the screen and the contact is marginal.
James (LAL) contests the driving shot attempt and incidental "high-five" contact occurs with Edwards (MIN) after the release.
Hachimura (LAL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Edwards's (MIN) driving shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) and Conley (MIN) engage and disengage during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Edwards' (MIN) shot attempt does not come into contact with the rim and the shot clock expires prior to Towns' (MIN) release of the put-back attempt. Possession is properly awarded to Los Angeles.
Davis (LAL) firms up on his left leg and marginal contact occurs with Conley (MIN) as he moves over the pick.
Conley (MIN) lowers his arm down and makes contact to Schroder's (LAL) arm/body and affects his driving shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) rests his hand on Schroder's (LAL) side and collapses his arm as he absorbs the marginal contact during the driving shot attempt.
Anderson (MIN) and Davis (LAL) come together during the loose ball and marginal contact occurs.
Anderson (MIN) locks and holds Davis' (LAL) right arm during the screen, which affects Davis' ability to disengage from the pick.
Hachimura (LAL) steps to his left and delivers contact that displaces Prince (MIN) during the pick.
Towns (MIN) raises his arm into Reaves' (LAL) arm as the two players engage in the paint and the contact is marginal.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Edward's (MIN) driving shot attempt.
Conley (MIN) extends his hand to the ball and deflects it away from Russell (LAL) during the inbound. The arm contact after the deflection is incidental.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Prince's (MIN) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) commits a take foul on Reaves (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of the fourth quarter or overtime.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) commits a take foul on Schroder (LAL).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Anderson's (MIN) pass goes out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Los Angeles.
Anderson (MIN) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
Schroder (LAL) brings his arm around Edwards' (MIN) side and the contact is marginal.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) perimeter jump shot attempt.
